class":"no-margin"},{"type":"image","url":"https://downloads.intercomcdn.com/i/o/126851177/77acc034a0e4b6c66c1c6089/Screen_Shot_2019-06-10_at_10_00_54_AM_1.png","width":1960,"height":1582,"align":"center"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"To edit action settings, go to\u003cb\u003e [Page name] \u0026gt; [Page Type] Settings\u003c/b\u003e. These settings are always located the third tab to the right. Note, each type of action page's settings will look a little different, but the key components outlined throughout the rest of this document will always be there.¬†","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"heading","text":"Step 2: Set up auto-tags","idAttribute":"step-2-set-up-auto-tags"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"You should \u003ca href=\"https://support.nationbuilder.com/people/gather-profiles/how-to-use-tags\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003eautomatically add tags\u003c/a\u003e to any person who takes an action on your website. Why? Tags are virtual sticky notes added to a profile to describe a characteristic or action the person has taken. They make it easier to find specific groups of people, as well as provide for targeted and personalized communication. This may seem a little vague now, but we promise it will be insanely helpful in the future.¬†","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"For example, you can track attendance for an event by adding the tag ‚ÄúRSVP-Blood Drive-Event date‚Äù to anyone who RSVPs on your event page.\u0026nbsp;","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"image","url":"https://downloads.intercomcdn.com/i/o/126851307/eb8d662d7b4e1867c68da5e2/Screen_Shot_2019-06-10_at_10_00_54_AM_2.png","width":1960,"height":1582,"align":"center"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Under \u003cb\u003e[Page Type] Settings\u003c/b\u003e, type your tag(s) into the box labelled \"Tag all signups with.\" In this example, I am assigning all of the people who sign up on my website with the tag \"RSVP-blood drive-Feb 19.\" Make sure to separate multiple tags with commas. Click \u003cb\u003eSave settings\u003c/b\u003e.","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Once this tag is set up and people have signed up online, you will be able to see this tag on their profile.\u0026nbsp;","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"image","url":"https://downloads.intercomcdn.com/i/o/183234883/ae180f64b481d48a4a40a9a3/Screen+Shot+2020-02-07+at+1.39.37+PM.png","width":2348,"height":876},{"type":"paragraph","text":"You can also \u003ca href=\"https://nationbuilder.com/how_to_filter\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003efilter\u003c/a\u003e for the tag and find all of the people with it.¬†","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"image","url":"https://downloads.intercomcdn.com/i/o/183234956/4073339f947125962fee7518/Screen+Shot+2020-02-07+at+1.40.01+PM.png","width":2364,"height":1414},{"type":"heading","text":"Step 3: Assign a point person","idAttribute":"step-3-assign-a-point-person"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Assigning a point person when a visitor takes an action on your website is key. A point person is responsible for that visitor‚Äôs relationship with your organization.","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"For example, your volunteer coordinator would be an excellent point person for people who sign up on your volunteer page. Any \u003ca href=\"https://support.nationbuilder.com/settings/your-account/manage-control-panel-users\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003econtrol panel user\u003c/a\u003e can be listed as a point person.¬†","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","class":"no-margin"},{"type":"image","url":"http